## ⚖️ Comparative Analysis: Standard vs. Blind Minimization

To demonstrate the scientific value of this implementation, here is a structural comparison between the original standard evaluator and our new robust, blind evaluator:

| Metric / Feature | Standard (Cheating) Evaluator | Our Blind Minimization Evaluator |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Prior Knowledge** | Hardcoded target minimum coordinates ($x = -1.704$, $y = 0.678$). | **Absolute Zero.** Has no knowledge of any target coordinates or optimal value. |
| **Scoring Basis** | Euclidean distance to hardcoded target coordinate points. | **Relative Improvement** compared to the best member of the active population. |
| **Adaptability** | Locked to a single landscape. Changing the function breaks the scoring. | **Universally Adaptable** to any user-defined callable function signature. |
| **State Tracking** | Static thresholds. | **Dynamic Baseline Cache** persisted to disk (`_blind_baseline.json`) across subprocesses. |

